parameters.definition: Number of coins plated by process A
Number of coins plated by process B

description: There are two processes, process A and process B, to plate a coin with gold. Process A requires \param{GoldA} units of gold, \param{WireA} wires, and can plate \param{CoinsA} coins. Process B requires \param{GoldB} units of gold, \param{WireB} wires, and can plate \param{CoinsB} coins. There are \param{TotalGold} units of gold and \param{TotalWires} wires available. How many processes of each type should be run to maximize the total number of coins that can be plated?
